<!doctype html><html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-T004 Business Cleanup</title><style>body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;line-height:1.45;color:#111827}h1{color:#0f172a}h2{border-bottom:1px solid #cbd5e1;padding-bottom:4px}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;margin:12px 0}td,th{border:1px solid #cbd5e1;padding:8px;vertical-align:top}th{background:#e2e8f0}.note{background:#f8fafc;border-left:5px solid #22c55e;padding:10px;margin:12px 0}.small{font-size:12px;color:#475569}</style></head><body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - Business Cleanup Packet</h1><p><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T004<br><b>Package:</b> Business Cleanup Packet<br><b>Scenario:</b> Text-message quote mess to quote-to-deposit system</p><p><img src="../assets/sample-business-proof.svg" alt="Business tracker visual" style="width:100%;max-width:760px"></p><h2>Customer input received</h2><ul><li>Screenshots of old quotes and text-message approvals.</li><li>Short service list with inconsistent pricing and deposit requests.</li><li>Two sample invoices and several follow-up messages.</li><li>Owner wants fewer missed follow-ups and cleaner deposits.</li></ul><h2>Sorted process</h2><table><tr><th>Stage</th><th>Definition</th><th>Next action</th></tr><tr><td>New</td><td>Customer asked for help but no quote path yet.</td><td>Ask intake questions and request photos/details.</td></tr><tr><td>Need Info</td><td>Quote cannot be prepared safely.</td><td>Send missing-info message.</td></tr><tr><td>Quote Sent</td><td>Price/options sent to customer.</td><td>Follow up after 3 business days.</td></tr><tr><td>Approved</td><td>Customer accepted scope.</td><td>Request deposit or scheduling confirmation.</td></tr><tr><td>Deposit Paid</td><td>Work is build-ready.</td><td>Move to job queue and set due date.</td></tr></table><h2>Quote fields</h2><table><tr><th>Required field</th><th>Why it matters</th></tr><tr><td>Customer name/contact</td><td>Prevents lost leads.</td></tr><tr><td>Service requested</td><td>Connects quote to service menu.</td></tr><tr><td>Scope included</td><td>Defines what is being sold.</td></tr><tr><td>Not included</td><td>Prevents misunderstanding.</td></tr><tr><td>Price/options</td><td>Makes approval clear.</td></tr><tr><td>Deposit due</td><td>Defines when work becomes active.</td></tr><tr><td>Next follow-up date</td><td>Prevents dead quotes.</td></tr></table><h2>Sample follow-up wording</h2><div class="note">Hi [Name], just checking whether you want me to hold this quote open or make any changes. The next step would be [deposit / missing info / schedule choice]. Thanks.</div><h2>Customer-ready summary</h2><p>This cleanup gives every lead a status, next action, quote amount, deposit trigger, and follow-up date. The goal is not more software; it is one path that can be used every time.</p><p class="small">Highway 38 Solutions - Big problems. Clear plans. Hypothetical sample deliverable.</p></body></html>